task.summary:
Refactor and clean up codebase
This commit refactors the codebase for improved consistency, cleans up unused or redundant code, and updates various dependencies and build configurations.
- **Refactor `WeatherRepository`:** - Simplify `WeatherData` data class by removing location and clothing-specific fields. - Streamline `generateClothingAdvice` to return only the text and icon. - Remove location settings logic (`WeatherLocationSettings`, `saveLocationSettings`, `locationSettingsFlow`).
- **Cleanup `WeatherWorker`:** - Remove complex location-based weather simulation. - Simplify to generate random temperature and precipitation and save it. - Standardize the worker's unique name and scheduling policy.
- **Code Formatting and Cleanup:** - Apply consistent formatting (tabs to spaces) across multiple Kotlin files (`.kt`), XML layouts, and Gradle scripts (`.kts`). - Remove redundant code and comments.
- **Build & Dependency Updates:** - Update `compileSdk` and `targetSdk` to 36. - Set Kotlin JVM toolchain to version 21. - Upgrade various dependencies, including Glance, Navigation-Compose, and lifecycle libraries. - Add `foojay-resolver-convention` plugin in `settings.gradle.kts`.

Refactor and clean up codebase
This commit refactors the codebase for improved consistency, cleans up unused or redundant code, and updates various dependencies and build configurations.
- **Refactor `WeatherRepository`:** - Simplify `WeatherData` data class by removing location and clothing-specific fields. - Streamline `generateClothingAdvice` to return only the text and icon. - Remove location settings logic (`WeatherLocationSettings`, `saveLocationSettings`, `locationSettingsFlow`).
- **Cleanup `WeatherWorker`:** - Remove complex location-based weather simulation. - Simplify to generate random temperature and precipitation and save it. - Standardize the worker's unique name and scheduling policy.
- **Code Formatting and Cleanup:** - Apply consistent formatting (tabs to spaces) across multiple Kotlin files (`.kt`), XML layouts, and Gradle scripts (`.kts`). - Remove redundant code and comments.
- **Build & Dependency Updates:** - Update `compileSdk` and `targetSdk` to 36. - Set Kotlin JVM toolchain to version 21. - Upgrade various dependencies, including Glance, Navigation-Compose, and lifecycle libraries. - Add `foojay-resolver-convention` plugin in `settings.gradle.kts`.

Refactor: Rename package and remove theme/settings UI
- **Package Renaming:** Changed the application's package name from `com.example.stalp` to `com.dagsbalken.app` across all relevant files, including manifests, build scripts, and source code. - **UI Removal:** Deleted `SettingsScreen.kt` and its associated theme files (`Color.kt`, `Theme.kt`). This removes the in-app settings UI for theme and location selection. - **Build Configuration:** - Updated `build.gradle.kts` by lowering `minSdk` to 21, setting Java compatibility to version 17, and removing outdated build configurations. - Added `desugar_jdk_libs` to support modern Java APIs on older Android versions. - Updated various library versions in `libs.versions.toml`. - **Project Configuration:** - Changed the project's root name to "Stalp" in `settings.gradle.kts`. - Updated IDE settings (`.idea/` files) to align with the new JDK 17 and package structure.

Rename app and theme from Stalp to Dagsbalken and add initial scaffolding for theming.
- Rename the app and widget from "Stalp" to "Dagsbalken" in `strings.xml`. - Update the application theme name from `Theme.Stalp` to `Theme.Dagsbalken` in `themes.xml`. - Introduce initial files for theming and UI components: - Add `DagsbalkenTheme.kt` and `ThemeOption.kt` to define and manage different visual themes. - Create `DagsbalkenIcons.kt` with a set of standard `ImageVector` icons for use in the app. - Add a placeholder `SettingsScreen.kt` for future theme selection UI. - Define the `DayEvent.kt` data class.
Add WeatherLocationSettings data class and methods for saving location settings and weather data
